Class Blog

java.lang.Object
com.cb.backend.model.Blog
@Entity public class Blog extends Object
Entity Blog represents a blog post stored in the database.

This entity is mapped to the CB_BLOGS table and is used to store blog articles created by users. A blog post contains title, thumbnail, description, article content and information about creation and update timestamps.

Each blog post is associated with exactly one User.

Since:
1.0
Author:
Dmytro Babich
